  <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Sleeps 38 - 40 guests</strong></p>
<p>This delightful free-standing chalet built in traditional stone and wood occupies a quiet location on the edge of the main village centre, just a 3 minute walk to the selection of restaurants, bars and shops in this pretty, friendly resort. For complete ski convenience, a complimentary minibus shuttle service runs to the lifts and back. A free local bus service is also available, with a bus stop directly outside the chalet.</p>
<p>The open-plan lounge and dining room is full of charm and character, with exposed beams and an open fireplace. Enjoy afternoon tea or an apéritif from the large sunny terrace off the dining room, overlooking the fantastic views across the valley to Les Arcs. The bedrooms are all a good size and have their own private en suite facilities, most benefit from a balcony with spectacular views. There are two suites available, comprising a double and twin bedroom and bathroom, both rooms have a balcony. The chalet is ideal for groups of friends or families. See our <a data-udi="umb://document/828e4c33a3674f48b9358960a2eb57bb" href="/{localLink:umb://document/828e4c33a3674f48b9358960a2eb57bb}" title="Group Ski Holidays">groups page</a> which has details of generous discounts and our Groups Hotline, and don’t forget that our Inghams Plus offers of 2-for-1 ski/snowboard hire and early booking discounts on lift passes also apply to groups!</p>
<p>La Rosière is an excellent choice for families, see our <a data-udi="umb://document/b2d4d8c45f52419a930b506f14a670df" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b2d4d8c45f52419a930b506f14a670df}" title="Chalet, 'Xtra Chalet' &amp; Chalet Hotel Holidays">chalet &amp; Chalet Hotels' page </a>for full details.</p>]]></description>
